snippet.textDisplay: Just Imagine if Tyson Fury lost that fight by KO or TKO after that walkout or a walkout in which he had an outfit looking similar in size and weight to that of Wilders and then stated that his legs weren’t right. Can you imagine the ridicule that man would get. Immediately after that fight Deontay was quick to say no excuses but they started coming out anyways and then a day or so later he tells “Yahoo Sports” that his  suit put a leg workout on him that it compromised his ability and fatigued his leg strength, if that was the other way Wilder and everyone would have laughed Fury and his pillow hands back to the UK. I knew that when Fury said he hired nutritionist George Lockhart and he was having his meals prepared, abstaining from all temptations he would be significantly better and most importantly more confident doing something nutritionally that he’d never done before as a HW not to mention a seriously more experienced trainer like Javan”SugarHill” Steward. I have to say when Anthony Joshua got dropped and finished by a massive dog Ruiz he made no excuses.  Congratulated Andy, let him enjoy his moment in boxing history, came back and schooled him. Deontay should have learned something from that.
